entries.meaning: (chiefly Canada, US) While being born or produced. [First attested in the mid 20th century.]
examples: This festival is an excellent chance to see new talent aborning.

entries.meaning: (chiefly Canada, US) That is in the process of being born; coming into existence; before coming to completion. [First attested in the mid 20th century.]
examples: No fewer than five planned “uprisings” died a-borning.
